dataIdInfo.idAbs: This database maintains polygon information on parcels that are conserved for the purpose of protecting the open space and natural habitats in San Diego County. For each property, the database provides the preserve’s name, owner, and manager along with more detailed land information where available.
dataIdInfo.idPurp: To provide a comprehensive inventory of the land in the region that is conserved for the purpose of protecting the open space and natural habitats including lands inside and outside of NCCP areas. Conserved lands are those lands that are legal converved to: Protect natural habitats, species, and open space (including agricultural lands that are important components of the regional habitat preserve design); Contribute to the existing and planned regional habitat preserve system; and Managed to protect the open space or naturlal resources into the future.

themeKeys.keyword: Conserved Lands, Protected Areas, Preserves, Habitat

dataIdInfo.suppInfo: Stacked polygons for condos and timeshares. Source: SanGIS Imported to LIS GDB from SanGIS SDE. SanGIS online metadata at http://66.121.127.165/file_store/Parcels%20and%20Lots/Parcels.pdf Parcel Zone and Land Use codes are used by County appraisers. They are not well maintained and are not considered reliable for other purposes. Please use the landuse layer for this information (supplied to us by SANDAG). Use the zoning layer for zoning in the County unincorporated areas. Contact the appropriate city for other zoning information. Most of the parcel attributes are joined to SanGIS graphics from County Assessor files and are updated weekly. SanGIS does not enter ownership information. If you detect errors in the attributes, we can pass those along to the Assessor but we cannot make the changes ourselves. We will make corrections to the polygon boundaries and APNs. The parcel_all layer now includes condominium records. If you use the identify tool on a condo polygon you will see multiple ownership records displayed for the condo owners. The parcels are also now multi-part. If a parcel is split by a right-of-way for example, the two parts are linked and share attributes.

Consts.useLimit: This database should not be used as a primary source of information on conserved lands. This database is a compilation of multiple primary sources.
